“Looking for fuel.” You pull yourself up into the hatch. “We have to torch the ship.”

You hear a soft hiss, and the sound of her boots on the grating. The marshal’s hand grabs your leg to haul you out of the crawlspace. “You will not.” Before you can argue you’re in cuffs again.

