Karissa looks at you, and you can make out the glimmer of blood on her face. “It is nothing.” She holsters her sidearm.

“Shit. You’re bleeding.” You run up to her, trying to get a better look. “Let me see your head.”

Karissa scoffs. “I am fine. Did it get you?” She grabs your shoulders, looking you over. “Your back?” She turns you to look at your shredded jacket.

“It didn’t get me; would you just lean down so I can take a look?” You push her arm away and shed your destroyed jacket. Karissa huffs and drops to a knee, giving you a clear view of her head. A neat row of claw marks scores down the side of her face. It only just missed her right eye. “Well, it’s not too deep.” You tear off a patch from your jacket, and start wiping the blood away. “Let’s wash it out at the stream.” 

